arnered a friendship with jay leno a famed car enthusiast and also to his ownership of the corvette produced for the fiftieth anniversary of that automobile now hes honored with the m eugene merchant manufacturing medal of asmesme given to an exceptional individual who has had significant influence on and responsibility for improving the productivity and efficiency of the manufacturing operation mr cowger had a year career  with general motors he has held several senior positions at general motors including president and managing director of gm de mexico  chairman of adam opel ag  group vice president of manufacturing and labor relations  and president of gm north america  prior to his retirement in  mr cowger was group vice president of general motors global manufacturing and labor relations  in this position he was responsible for directing all of gm’s manufacturing manufacturing engineering and labor relations activities worldwide and was a member of the automotive strategy board and the automotive product board mr cowger began his career at the gm assembly division plant in kansas city ks as a coop student of general motors institute he held various manufacturing and engineering positions at the fairfax plant in kansas city and the oldsmobile division in lansing mi before being appointed plant manager of the wentzville assembly center in missouri in  and complex manager at the lordstown oh assembly and stamping plants in  in  he was appointed manufacturing manager for the cadillac division and was instrumental in cadillacs winning the malcolm baldrige award he also was executiveincharge of advanced manufacturing engineering at the gm technical center mr cowger continues making contributions to industry as chairman and chief executive officer of glc ventures llc a bloomfield hills mi management consultancy on business manufacturing and technology strategy he is chairman of the board of trustees at kettering university and serves on the board of directors of delphi corp over the past  years mr cowger has contributed many articles to publications participated in press interviews and presented keynote speeches at numerous forums mr cowger received his bachelors degree in industrial engineering from general motors institute he earned his masters degree in management from the massachusetts institute of technology in  he holds an honorary doctorate of humane letters  from lindenwood college and an honorary doctorate of engineering  from kettering university under gary cowgers leadership of its manufacturing system gm saw overall productivity improve  percent over six years share asme getmediaaafeadffaafgarycowgerthumbpngaspxwidthheightextpng march  by asmeorg related media video oil and gas where we are now asmeorg podcast dual fuel engines for hydraulic fracturing asmeorg video offshore drilling and the energy future asmeorg articles home on the shales me magazine  comment hydraulic fracturing mature technology modern marvel mark crawford asmeorg fracking a look back michael macrae asmeorg  comment resources bpvcv   bpvc section vnondestructive examination standard  bpvcviii   bpvc section viiirules for construction of pr standard  bpvcviii   bpvc section viiirules for construction of pr standard  asme membership learn more receive exclusive resources and a free me magazine subscription discounts on training conferences  publications and join thousands of dedicated engineers more about asme – the americansociety of mechanical engineers featured topics bioengineering career  education design  manufacturing power  energy standards  certification technology  society all topics site map events conferences competitions committee meetings calendar about us news membership get involved advocacy foundation careers at asme me magazine press shop asme standards certifications courses journals proceedings books shop all shopping cart  utility cs connect ca connect journal tool job board directory sign in or register home contact terms of u