anager for the cadillac division and was instrumental in cadillac winning the malcolm baldrige award he was then appointed executiveincharge of advance manufacturing engineering at the gm technical center mr cowgers senior positions at general motors included president and managing director of gm de mexico  chairman of adam opel ag  group vice president of manufacturing and labor relations  and president of gm north america  prior to his retirement following his  year career mr cowger was group vice president of global manufacturing and labor relations  in this position he was responsible for directing all of gms manufacturing  major facilities in  countries manufacturing engineering and labor relations activities worldwide and was a member of the automotive strategy board and the automotive product board mr cowger was instrumental in leading the development of several manufacturing technologies including the use of mathbased tools along with the adoption of synchronous and lean manufacturing at general motors mr cowger was elected to the national academy of engineering  for his contributions to the gm global manufacturing system which has dramatically improved flexibility quality and productivity in automotive manufacturing he is currently serving on the committee for advanced vehicles and fuels a study being conducted for a report to congress sponsored by the national science foundation mr cowger has served on many boards and continues to serve on nonprofit boards in the detroit area among his honors he received the eugene merchant manufacturing medal of asmesme in  he was selected automotive industries executive of the year  received the society of automotive engineers manufacturing leadership award  and the shienming wu foundations wu manufacturing leadership award  mr cowger received his bachelors degree in engineering at general motors institute now kettering university in flint michigan in  he earned his masters degree in management at the massachusetts institute of technology as a sloan fellow in cambridge mass in  he holds an honorary doctorate of humane letters degree  from lindenwood college st charles missouri and an honorary doctor of engineering  from kettering university   administration program directors and coordinators isd faculty affiliated faculty short program instructors staff design science community isd external advisory board gsac az list employment   contact us locations  maps facebook twitter linkedin youtube tagboard umichisd college of engineering university of michigan privacy policy isd intranet faculty resources   the regents of the university of michigan gary l cowger to receive the m eugene merchant manufacturing medal please enable javascript     learn more internet explorer  firefox  chrome  safari asme is built with the most modern web standards which give you a better  more reliable experience communities  membership connect with us asme on twitter asme on facebook asme on linkedin all topics bioengineering career  education design  manufacturing power  energy standards  certification technology  society all topics events conferences competitions committee meetings calendar about us news membership get involved advocacy foundation careers at asme me magazine shop asme standards certifications courses journals proceedings books shop all sign in or create account  search type site people groups seary query search gary l cowger to receive the m eugene merchant manufacturing medal new york nov   – gary l cowger a resident of bloomfield hills mich and chairman and chief executive officer of glc ventures llc will be honored by the american society of mechanical engineers asme and the society of manufacturing engineers sme  he is being recognized for leadership and technical contributions in developing and implementing advanced manufacturing systems to enhance flexibility quality and productivity in all gm plants he will receive the m eugene merchant manufacturing medal of asmesme the medal established in  honors an exceptional individual who has had significant influence and responsibility for improving the productivity and efficiency of the manufacturing operation  the award will be presented to mr cowger at the  asme honors assembly held during the society’s international mechanical engineering congress and exposition in vancouver british columbia nov  through  following a year career  with general motors cowger continues making industry contributions through glc ventures llc a management consultancy on business manufacturing and technology strategy  additionally he is chairman of the board of trustees at kettering university flint mich a coop college that was formerly known as general motors institute and he serves on the board of directors of delphi corporation troy mich a global supplier of electronics and technologies for automotive commercial vehicles and other market segments  cowger began his career at the gm assembly division plant kansas city kan as a coop student at general motors institute  he held various manufacturing and engineering positions at the fairfax plant kansas city kan and oldsmobile division lansing mich before being appointed plant manager of the wentzville assembly center in missouri in  and complex manager at the lordstown ohio assembly and stamping plants in   in  he was appointed manufacturing manager for the cadillac division and was instrumental in cadillac winning the malcolm baldrige award  he also was executiveincharge of advanced manufacturing engineering at the gm technical center senior positions at general motors included president and managing director of gm de mexico  chairman of adam opel ag  group vice president of manufacturing and labor relations  and president of gm north america   prior to his retirement cowger was group vice president of general motors global manufacturing and labor relations  in this position he was responsible for directing all of gm’s manufacturing manufacturing engineering and labor relations activities worldwide and was a member of the automotive strategy board and the automotive product board cowger was instrumental in leading the development of several manufacturing technologies including the use of mathbased tools along with the adoption of synchronous and lean manufacturing at general motors  he oversaw the development of cflex a numerically controlled location device that allows multiple modelsstyles of body panels including doors underbodies side panels and roofs to be welded in subassembly in the body shop with the same set of programmable tools and robots  he worked with academic researchers at the university of michigan on the mm program which focused on reducing variations in vehicle manufacturing processes improving final fit and finish and enhancing product quality he was elected to the national academy of engineering for his contributions to the gm global manufacturing system which has dramatically improved flexibility quality and productivity in automotive manufacturing  under his leadership gm’s overall productivity improved  percent over the past six years over the last  years cowger has contributed many articles and publications participated in press interviews and presented keynote speeches at numerous forums among his honors cowger was named a fellow of stanford university california  becoming only the fifth recipient of this honor in  years  he was selected automotive industries’ executive of the year  and received the society of automotive engineers’ manufacturing leadership award  and the shienming wu foundation’s wu manufacturing leadership award  cowger received his bachelor’s degree in industrial engineering at general motors institute now kettering university in flint mich in   he earned his master’s degree in management at the massachusetts institute of technology cambridge in   he holds an honorary doctorate of humane letters degree  from lindenwood college st charles mo and an honorary doctor of engineering  from kettering university about asmeasme helps the global engineering community develop solutions to real world challenges  founded in  as the american society of mechanical engineers asme is a notforprofit professional organization that enables collaboration knowledge sharing and skill development across all engineering disciplines while promoting the vital role of the engineer in society  asme codes and standards publications conferences continuing education and professional development programs provide a foundation for advancing technical knowledge and a safer world  honors  awards achievement awards literature awards service awards unit awards fellows general information press releases asme membership learn more receive exclusive resources and a free me magazine subscription discounts on training conferences  publications and join thousands of dedicated engineers more about asme – the americansociety of mechanical engineers featured topics bioengineering career  education design  manufacturing power  energy standards  certification technology  society all topics site map events conferences competitions committee meetings calendar about us news membership get involved advocacy foundation careers at asme me magazine press shop asme standards certifications courses journals proceedings books shop all shopping cart  utility cs connect ca connect journal tool job board directory sign in or register home contact terms of use privacy statement about this site community rules  the american society of mechanical engineers share generic post to your profile post to your profile post to your group post to your groups you must select a location to post to start typing the name of the group name you must select a group to post to comment share cancel share generic profile post to your profile groups post to your groups you must select a location to post to start typing the name of the group name you must select a group to post to comment share cancel this generic has been shared dlph